00:13:28.050 --> 00:13:30.120
STUDENT: [INAUDIBLE]

00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:30.390
PROFESSOR: Um-hmm.

00:13:30.390 --> 00:13:37.340
So, it's talking about
bond enthalpies.

00:13:37.340 --> 00:13:40.000
And when we talk about bond
enthalpy, the symbol that we

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:43.310
see for a bond enthalpy
is usually delta h.

00:13:43.310 --> 00:13:45.190
And this is where all the
confusion starts, because

00:13:45.190 --> 00:13:48.020
everything's delta h, it just
depends on the subscript here,

00:13:48.020 --> 00:13:50.310
right, what kind of delta
h we're talking about.

00:13:50.310 --> 00:13:52.680
In the case of bond enthalpy
often you'll see no

00:13:52.680 --> 00:13:54.520
subscript at all.

00:13:54.520 --> 00:13:57.250
But sometimes you do see a
subscript, which would then

00:13:57.250 --> 00:14:01.050
just be delta h sub b here.

00:14:01.050 --> 00:14:03.940
So if we're trying to do this
calculation based on bond

00:14:03.940 --> 00:14:09.700
