for now I just want you to

00:24:07.570 --> 00:24:09.780
think about the fact that in
addition to thinking about

00:24:09.780 --> 00:24:11.590
enthalpy there's this
other term here

00:24:11.590 --> 00:24:13.090
that comes into play.

00:24:13.090 --> 00:24:16.820
So when we're talking about what
the sign about delta g is

00:24:16.820 --> 00:24:19.960
or free energy is, some of you
might already be familiar with

00:24:19.960 --> 00:24:22.730
this, when we're talking about
a negative delta g, is this

00:24:22.730 --> 00:24:27.570
spontaneous or non-spontaneous.

00:24:27.570 --> 00:24:30.740
So, maybe not so familiar,
which is totally fine.

00:24:30.740 --> 00:24:33.570
So in terms of thinking about
a negative delta g, that's

00:24:33.570 --> 00:24:35.840
going to be a spontaneous
process.

00:24:35.840 --> 00:24:38.940
Any time you see a negative free
energy, which just like

00:24:38.940 --> 00:24:40.800
when we talk about entropy, it's
a similar idea, it means

00:24:40.800 --> 00:24:44.730
that free energy is released
as the reaction progresses.

00:24:44.730 --> 00:24:47.360
That's going to be a spontaneous
process.

00:24:47.360 --> 00:24:50.140
So that means that if delta g
is greater than zero, then

00:24:50.140 --> 00:24:53.560
what we're going to see a
non-spontaneous process.

00:24:53.560 --> 00:24:56.900
And finally in the case where
delta g is equal to zero, at

00:24:56.900 --> 00:24:59.050
this point we're at equilibrium,
which basically

00:24:59.050 --> 00:25:01.870
means that there's no net change
in either the forward

00:25:01.870 --> 00:25:05.500
or the reverse reaction in
terms of thinking about

00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:07.300
whether something's
spontaneous or not

00:25:07.300 --> 00:25:09.430
spontaneous, it's just
at equilibrium

00:25:09.430 --> 00:25:11.470
we see no net change.

00:25:11.470 --> 00:25:14.020
And something I want to point
out is that this reaction is

00:25:14.020 --> 00:25:16.290
valid only when where at
constant temperature and

00:25:16.290 --> 00:25:20.020
pressure, which we will be
throughout the discussions in

00:25:20.020 --> 00:25:22.650
this class in terms of
using this equation.

00:25:22.650 --> 00:25:25.510
And also, it turns out that
when you do most chemical

00:25:25.510 --> 00:25:28.940
equations, you are, in fact,
at a pretty constant

00:25:28.940 --> 00:25:31.860
temperature, and a constant
pressure in terms of most

00:25:31.860 --> 00:25:34.180
things are done in the open
atmosphere, so that's really

00:25:34.180 --> 00:25:35.150
not going to change.

00:25:35.150 --> 00:25:39.320
All right, so let's just talk
very briefly about why it is

00:25:39.320 --> 00:25:42.480
that free energy is what
determines spontaneity, and

00:25:42.480 --> 00:25:44.350
not this enthalpy here,
not what the

00:25:44.350 --> 00:25:45.920
change in enthalpy is.

00:25:45.920 --> 00:25:48.600
And it really comes in terms
remembering it in terms of the

00:25:48.600 --> 00:25:49.200
definition.

00:25:49.200 --> 00:25:52.310
When we think about delta g,
what that is is that it's

00:25:52.310 --> 00:25:55.840
energy that's released or used
in the reaction, but if it is

00:25:55.840 --> 00:25:58.430
released, that it can directly
be used to do work.

00:25:58.430 --> 00:26:00.130
It's what we call free
energy -- it's

00:26:00.130 --> 00:26:01.920
free to do other things.

00:26:01.920 --> 00:26:04.680
Whereas when we were talking
about enthalpy here, well,

00:26:04.680 --> 00:26:07.300
this is the amount of heat
that's released when we break

00:26:07.300 --> 00:26:09.390
and form the bonds
in the reaction.

00:26:09.390 --> 00:26:12.840
But some of it actually gets
stuck in the molecules, and

00:26:12.840 --> 00:26:15.240
this is just a way to think
about it, this term here is

00:26:15.240 --> 00:26:17.580
one way we can think about it,
it's just some energy that's

00:26:17.580 --> 00:26:18.660
getting stuck.

00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:21.370
So, for example, molecules,
which we don't really go into

00:26:21.370 --> 00:26:23.990
