00:31:37.860 --> 00:31:40.490
I introduced it without
explaining at all

00:31:40.490 --> 00:31:41.960
what it really is.

00:31:41.960 --> 00:31:44.420
So let's take a few moments
and think about entropy.

00:31:44.420 --> 00:31:48.500
Entropy is actually a very easy
concept to think about,

00:31:48.500 --> 00:31:50.180
it's a measure of disorder.

00:31:50.180 --> 00:31:53.280
I think most of us have a very
good concept of how things

00:31:53.280 --> 00:31:56.090
tend to go to disorder, so
it's something we can

00:31:56.090 --> 00:31:59.320
conceptualize just in an
infinite number of ways.

00:31:59.320 --> 00:32:01.260
And entropy is simply
a measure of the

00:32:01.260 --> 00:32:02.850
disorder of a system.

00:32:02.850 --> 00:32:05.120
And when we're talking about
chemical reactions, what we're

00:32:05.120 --> 00:32:07.620
talking about is a change
in entropy.

00:32:07.620 --> 00:32:11.810
So whether, as a reaction goes
forward, are we becoming more

00:32:11.810 --> 00:32:16.110
ordered or are we becoming
more disordered?

00:32:16.110 --> 00:32:20.020
So just like we saw for
enthalpy, entropy also is a

00:32:20.020 --> 00:32:23.270
state function, so it doesn't
matter in terms of path how we

00:32:23.270 --> 00:32:25.260
got from point a to point b.

00:32:25.260 --> 00:32:27.680
All we need to worry about is
the current state of our

00:32:27.680 --> 00:32:31.000
system, what the current
entropy is and take the

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:32.350
difference.

00:32:32.350 --> 00:32:35.880
So, an example that I like to
use in terms of conceptually

00:32:35.880 --> 00:32:38.940
thinking about what's going on
in terms of disorder, and

00:32:38.940 --> 00:32:41.470
which is especially relevant
in New England is thinking

00:32:41.470 --> 00:32:43.510
about stone wall.

00:32:43.510 --> 00:32:46.880
So you can think about a stone
wall in terms of being very,

00:32:46.880 --> 00:32:47.940
very ordered, right.

00:32:47.940 --> 00:32:51.400
If you just built your stone
wall, every stone is in place,

00:32:51.400 --> 00:32:53.530
it has a high degree of order.

00:32:53.530 --> 00:32:56.710
So in other words, the
disorder is very low.

00:32:56.710 --> 00:33:01.140
So it has a low entropy, a
low level of disorder.

00:33:01.140 --> 00:33:03.950
But if we're looking at a New
England stone wall, which are

00:33:03.950 --> 00:33:06.370
typically found if you're hiking
in the woods you see

00:33:06.370 --> 00:33:10.100
ones that are just ancient and
are completely crumbling down,

00:33:10.100 --> 00:33:12.620
you'll find that the stone wall
is no longer quite so

00:33:12.620 --> 00:33:14.410
ordered as it was.

00:33:14.410 --> 00:33:17.940
In fact, let's say there's a
few stones that have fallen

00:33:17.940 --> 00:33:21.540
off, our disorder has increased,
so we end up

00:33:21.540 --> 00:33:23.890
increasing the entropy.

00:33:23.890 --> 00:33:26.365
And I do just want to point out
with this analogy that it

00:33:26.365 --> 00:33:27.690
is a state function.

00:33:27.690 --> 00:33:31.300
So for thinking about the change
in entropy, which is

00:33:31.300 --> 00:33:34.776
this distance right here, we
can either calculate it

00:33:34.776 --> 00:33:37.930
directly from here to here. but
it also doesn't matter,

00:33:37.930 --> 00:33:40.420
let's say the wall crumbled down
completely and we ended

00:33:40.420 --> 00:33:44.110
up having a very high degree of
disorder, if then someone

00:33:44.110 --> 00:33:47.620
put most of the stones back in
place and we went back down to

00:33:47.620 --> 00:33:50.290
this degree of disorder here,
it doesn't matter, it's a

00:33:50.290 --> 00:33:54.020
state function, all we care
about is the actual difference

00:33:54.020 --> 00:33:58.100
between our starting point
and our ending point.

00:33:58.100 --> 00:34:00.820
And I just can't resist putting
